  "body": "#### System information\r\nGeth version: `1.9.11-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Linux (Ubuntu 18.04)\r\nCommit hash : 6a62fe399b68ab9e3625ef5e7900394f389adc3a\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nAccount balance should be ETH 0.00001\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nAccount balance returns 0\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nI've installed Geth and ran it with light more. Serve is now synced regarding to the output below:  \r\n```\r\n> eth.syncing  \r\nfalse\r\n```\r\nI had a testing transaction on a generated account which its details is available [here](https://etherscan.io/address/0xd9de4af752b564e6d0d2d03d4a7c413b726c2ab0). But the given balance still returns 0  \r\n```\r\n> web3.fromWei(eth.getBalance('0xd9de4af752b564e6d0d2d03d4a7c413b726c2ab0'), 'ether')  \r\n0\r\n\r\n```",
